The paper discusses the development of scientific software, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and computational engineering (cs.CE) categories. The focus on sustainability, reproducibility, and extensibility suggests a potential connection to deep learning (cs.DL) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the collaboration between domain scientists and software engineers may involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC) considerations.
